==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: marine mine
<hw>ma*rine" mine`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A military explosive device designed to be placed on or under the
surface of a body of water, and to explode when ships pass nearby or
come in contact with it. Its function is to destroy enemy ships or deny
hostile naval forces access to certain areas of the sea, usually near
the shoreline. Also called <altname>underwater mine</altname> and
<altname>floating mine</altname>, and previously referred to as a
<altname>torpedo</altname> (See <er>torpedo</er>{2}
<sd>(a)</sd>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mariner</ent>⟦br⟧
